{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2734", "repo": "rails", "body": "I think the rationale is that there isn't always scope for developers to \"sign\" their work, whether it be for client, or personal, or design, or contractual reasons, whatever.\r\n\r\nhumans.txt is just a neat way to discreetly sign the work that's done behind the scenes, that, let's face it, is often not acknowledged.\r\n\r\n> why hurt discoverability on purpose?\r\n\r\nI think the point is less to hurt discoverability and more to have a place to put a colophon that's not directly related to the product/service/system being developed, but directly related to the people doing the work.", "_id": {"$oid": "523fa3adbd354364b9019b62"}, "issue_id": 2734, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1934885", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2734#issuecomment-1934885", "updated_at": "2011-08-29T18:46:01Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca", "login": "paulca", "gravatar_id": "b408c8d259cc9b98cf69da4afcad92fb", "html_url": "https://github.com/paulca", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/b408c8d259cc9b98cf69da4afcad92fb?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F310ce61c90f3a46e340ee8257bc70e93.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1229, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/paulca/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-08-29T18:46:01Z", "id": 1934885, "owner": "rails